1.title: Episode #2.1
1.plot: Members of a Christian congregation play matchmaker, helping a single female parishioner find love. Will their plans be thwarted when one of the bachelors turns out to be her ex's good friend? Natalie Grant hosts.

2.title: Episode #2.2
2.plot: David & Tamela Mann act as relationship experts when members of a Christian church play matchmaker and help a female congregant find love. When one bachelor gets defensive, will she find comfort in the arms of another? Natalie Grant hosts.

3.title: Episode #2.3
3.plot: A 33-year old male virgin looks for love as members of his church play matchmaker and help him find just the right woman. Season 1 dating couple Randy & Rhoda give him relationship advice. Natalie Grant hosts.

4.title: Episode #2.4
4.plot: Members of a Christian congregation help a nurse look for love by fixing her up on several blind dates. As she learns archery from one of the bachelors, will cupid's arrow find a way to her heart? Natalie Grant hosts.

5.title: Episode #2.5
5.plot: Musical artist Bo Bice is a guest matchmaker as members of a Christian congregation help a divorced Dad with three kids find love. Natalie Grant hosts.

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Members of a Christian church play matchmaker and help a female fitness buff find love. Is it too late for this former party girl, who is now healthy in body and soul, to get serious about finding someone? Natalie Grant hosts.

7.title: Episode #2.7
7.plot: Members of a Christian congregation work together to help a single Dad and basketball player find love. As church members play matchmaker, the bachelorettes work to "drive" him crazy as they test their compatibility. Natalie Grant hosts.

8.title: Episode #2.8
8.plot: Musical artist Tim Timmons is a guest matchmaker as members of a Christian congregation help a reformed party boy find love. Natalie Grant Hosts

1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Natalie Grant hosts as members of a Christian congregation play matchmaker in this competition to help a single parishioner find love. During the premiere episode, a Charlotte, NC bachelorette is lead through an obstacle course by each bachelor.

2.title: Goshen
2.plot: After a devastating illness knocked her out of the dating world for 2 years, Nicole hopes to get back out there.

3.title: Rock Hill
3.plot: Single mother and reformed party girl Valeria has stayed away from men for years, but is ready to give it a try again.

4.title: Baltimore
4.plot: Iquasia has fallen for liars and players in the past, but now she's hoping to change her luck at church.

5.title: Milwaukee
5.plot: Sweet single mom Hilary, committed to her 2 year old, has stopped making time for herself.

6.title: Oxnard
6.plot: Shawna is a teacher whose busy work life has shut down her love life.

7.title: Tempe
7.plot: A very special episode featuring a bachelor, Randy, who is trying to get past a family tragedy and start a real relationship.

8.title: Brooklyn
8.plot: Social worker Denise Michel had her heart broken, but found joy again with this congregation and is now ready to find love.

imdb.plot outline: Each episode takes the Grammy award singer Natalie Grant to a church to match up one of their eligible singles. The church and pastor pick the guinea pig who then consents. Various "matchmakers" in the church nominate eligible dates, someone they think would be good and describe before the church why they picked the candidate. Then the guy says a few words and the church then narrows the field down to 3 finalists through ballot voting. The pastor picks a 4th candidate and the spotlighted single then spends time with all 4 doing a charity or other pre-selected activity. After that, the pastor selects a filtering game or interview process to observe the candidates and give insights into strengths and weaknesses, such that it's narrowed down to 3. Then, the single picks two finalists to date with the whole process and dates on camera. She evaluates with the audience pros and cons and what she's thinking and looking for, all the way along. Finally, she selects the winner to continue dating. It's a fun show giving many insights into relationships, thinking through the dating process with friendly voices feeding into it, for consideration.
